  "texts": [
    "This validates our hypothesis that taxonomic constraints mitigate LLM hallucinations while preserving recall.",
    "Isolating Relationship Extraction While removing the relationship extraction task marginally improves NER relaxed F1 (+4.2%; 0.501→0.522) and EL F1 (+3.3%; 0.367→0.379), these gains come at the expense of losing all relationship semantics critical for KG applications.",
    "Crucially, maintaining separate NER/EL and relationship stages doubles LLM computational costs due to redundant prompt processing.",
    "Our experiments suggest practitioners may prioritize relationship extraction when domain interactions are mission-critical (e.g., climate analysis), while considering the NER/EL-only approach for resource-constrained entity-centric use cases.",
    "Model Scale Larger models (70B vs. 8B) improve NER F1 by 33% (0.395 → 0.525), as increased model size better captures domain nuances."
